<section xmlns="https://code.dccouncil.us/schemas/dc-library" xmlns:codified="https://code.dccouncil.us/schemas/codified" xmlns:codify="https://code.dccouncil.us/schemas/codify" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">
  <num>24-221.05</num>
  <heading proof="needed">Reporting requirement.</heading>
  <para>
    <num undesignated="true">(a)</num>
    <text>The Department of Corrections shall:</text>
    <para>
      <num>(1)</num>
      <text>Regularly inform incarcerated persons of all awards, forfeitures, and restorations of good time credits; and</text>
    </para>
    <para>
      <num>(2)</num>
      <text>Inform the United States Parole Commission of all incarcerated persons:</text>
      <para>
        <num>(A)</num>
        <text>Who are expected to become eligible for release on parole within 45 days of their eligibility date; and</text>
      </para>
      <para>
        <num>(B)</num>
        <text>Whose release on parole will become mandatory within 45 days of the date when their release on parole becomes mandatory.</text>
      </para>
    </para>
  </para>
